00:46.146 --> 00:48.146
<i>Is there anything</i>
<i>you'd like to talk about?</i>

00:48.180 --> 00:50.480
Not really.

00:50.514 --> 00:53.282
<i>Every week you just sit</i>
<i>in silence on that couch.</i>

00:54.784 --> 00:58.019
- Do you know why you're here?
- I got caught.

00:58.054 --> 01:00.222
No, why you're here
with me.

01:01.991 --> 01:04.259
I have to go through you
to get parole.

01:04.293 --> 01:06.795
Well, in a manner
of speaking.

01:06.829 --> 01:08.964
It's my job
to evaluate you,

01:08.999 --> 01:11.124
the progress
of your rehabilitation.

01:11.158 --> 01:14.653
Come on, you really think
anyone in here gets rehabilitated?

01:14.687 --> 01:16.254
I think we rehabilitate
ourselves.

01:19.290 --> 01:21.791
You've been in here
for what now, seven years?

01:21.825 --> 01:24.691
- Yeah, something like that.
- You've had your share of fights.

01:24.725 --> 01:27.092
It's kind of what
we do in here.

01:27.126 --> 01:29.160
You're eligible for parole
in four months.

01:29.195 --> 01:31.162
I would think a man
of your obvious intelligence

01:31.196 --> 01:33.930
and skill would at least
create the impression

01:33.965 --> 01:35.716
of cooperation with me
to manipulate me into

01:35.741 --> 01:37.433
recommending parole.

01:37.434 --> 01:41.468
Well, maybe I just know
not to bullshit a bullshitter.

01:41.502 --> 01:42.247
<i>Fair enough.</i>

01:42.272 --> 01:44.418
<i>But believe it or not,</i>
<i>I am here to help you.</i>

01:44.738 --> 01:46.104
Yeah, right.

01:46.138 --> 01:48.773
I'm just another file
you got to process

01:48.807 --> 01:51.174
before you go home
to your cats.

01:51.209 --> 01:53.943
What makes you think
I have cats?

01:53.978 --> 01:56.044
Well, I know
you have a cat.

01:56.079 --> 01:58.378
Cats was a guess.

01:58.412 --> 02:00.211
What else?

02:00.246 --> 02:03.847
You're wearing a black bra
under a white blouse again.

02:03.882 --> 02:05.982
It's happened before,

02:06.017 --> 02:09.018
so it's not because you
didn't get your laundry done.

02:09.051 --> 02:11.586
If that were the case,
you'd go with no bra.

02:11.620 --> 02:15.156
<i>Your tits aren't that big.</i>

02:15.190 --> 02:18.124
<i>No, you deliberately</i>
<i>project your sexuality.</i>

02:18.158 --> 02:22.157
Maybe because
of a recent breakup

02:22.192 --> 02:24.092
or a divorce.

02:24.127 --> 02:27.395
<i>Either way, you get off</i>

02:27.430 --> 02:30.131
<i>on sitting across from men </i>
<i>who haven't seen a woman in years</i>

02:30.165 --> 02:31.966
knowing that we're gonna
go back to our cells

02:32.000 --> 02:34.635
and rub one out
thinking of you.

02:34.669 --> 02:38.638
<i>I mean, why else would</i>
<i>a woman that looks like you</i>

02:38.672 --> 02:40.740
work in a place like this?

02:43.343 --> 02:45.778
And, yeah, you have cats.

02:45.812 --> 02:49.547
Every time you wear
dark clothing like that navy pantsuit

02:49.582 --> 02:52.248
that you had tailored to cling
to your ass like a second skin,

02:52.283 --> 02:54.483
I see hairs on you.

02:54.518 --> 02:57.018
You're exceptionally
observant.

02:57.052 --> 02:58.752
- Occupational hazard.
- <i>Of a thief.</i>

02:58.787 --> 03:00.721
- Inmate.
- Are you gonna steal again?

03:00.755 --> 03:01.888
- No.
- Are you sure?

03:01.922 --> 03:04.124
- It's a trick question.
- <i>Why so?</i>

03:04.158 --> 03:06.993
If I say no,
I'm full of shit.

03:07.027 --> 03:09.895
If I say yes,
I don't get parole.

03:09.930 --> 03:13.032
Not everything's a trap.

03:14.368 --> 03:17.036
Never say that to a man
who's living in a cell.

03:19.973 --> 03:21.573
I like you.

03:23.510 --> 03:25.277
Isn't that
against the rules?

03:26.846 --> 03:28.447
Yes.

